Q8. What are the rules for a table to be in 1NF, 2NF, and 3NF?

Answer-

#1NF (First Normal Form) Rules
-Rule 1- Each table cell should contain a single(atomic) value.
-Rule 2- Each record needs to be unique.

#2NF (Second Normal Form) Rules
-Rule 1- Be in 1NF
-Rule 2- Single Column Primary Key that does not functionally dependant on 
any subset of candidate key relation
(it should not have Partial Dependency).

#3NF (Third Normal Form) Rules
-Rule 1- Be in 2NF
-Rule 2- Has no transitive functional dependencies